OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCroydon tram crash: TfL to 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fadmit to failings over     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffatal derailment           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Transport for London (TfL) has         
OL,6, indicated it will plead guilty to      
OL,7, health and safety failings over the    
OL,8, Croydon tram crash.                    
OL,10,FSeven passengers died and 61 were      
OL,11,Finjured when a tram derailed in south  
OL,12,FLondon on 9 November 2016.             
OL,14,FDriver Alfred Dorris, 48, of Beckenham,
OL,15,Falso appeared at the hearing at Croydon
OL,16,FMagistrates' Court.                    
OL,18,FHe indicated a not guilty plea to an   
OL,19,Fallegation of failing as an employee to
OL,20,Ftake reasonable care of passengers.    
